Just like its previous editions, the July 2 Roast and Rhyme event will be at Jahazi Pier in the posh Kampala suburb of Munyonyo.The festival is the brainchild of Swangz Avenue boss Julius Kyazze. It's an evening experience where you bring as much meat as possible, roast or have it roasted for you as you enjoy live music and the carnivore-like atmosphere.This time, it will be under the theme 'Story Tellers'. The festival will be headlined by singers Naava Grey and Kenneth Mugabi, and Janzi band. Ykee Benda will also be on the stage.Radio personalities Roger Mugisha and Cleopatra Kyoheirwe will host the event. Entrance is Shs 50,000.